imdb.plot: One newcomer red blood cell just wants to do her job. Between bacteria incursions and meeting a certain white blood cell, she's got a lot to learn.

episodes.title: Bump
episodes.plot: While chasing a germ that thinks its cuteness will protect it, U-1146 meets Backward-Cap, a novice platelet who aims to become stronger. A sudden incident in the temple's area causes a breaking of capillaries, and the platelets must stop the internal hemorrhage, with some coaxing from Megakaryocyte (cell that produces platelets). Megakaryocyte at first berates them for being weak, then motivates them by offering medals. The platelets form human chains to reach across the injury and seal it with a clot.

episodes.title: Acquired Immunity/Peyer's Patch
episodes.plot: Memory Cell sees a dream where the arrival of messengers from the outside signal the end of this world - As if his dream became reality, unidentified enemies enter the body. Will this world be ruined as Memory Cell predicts?

episodes.title: Dengue Fever/Acne
episodes.plot: Toxic reaction found on the epidermis. Mast Cell does her job according to the manual, but complaints pour in from other cells that are annoyed by her actions. Mast Cell loses her cool and unleashes her rage.

episodes.title: H. Pylori/Antigenic Shift
episodes.plot: An incident has occurred in the body. The Immune Cells rush to the scene and fight the cells infected by a virus. A group of mysterious bacteria appear in front of the Ordinary Cell and.

episodes.title: Cytokines
episodes.plot: Ordinary Cell heads to the intestines with White Blood Cell (Neutrophil) in search of the lactic acid bacteria. Ordinary Cell desperately searches for the lactic acid bacterium but is attacked by cells infected by a new virus.

episodes.title: Harmful Bacteria
episodes.plot: The antibody information of a cell has leaked. In the intestine, which has been irritated due to toxic gas being released by harmful bacteria, the group meets up with Memory T Cell who was formerly known as "Killer T Cell".

episodes.title: Pneumococcus
episodes.plot: The Red Blood Cell's delivery schedule is interrupted by invading pneumococci bacteria. After a White Blood Cell rescues her, she gets a surprise.

episodes.title: Scrape Wound
episodes.plot: A scrape puts a major dent in the Red Blood Cell's job, but she gets to meet the White Blood Cell again as he fights the invading bacteria and viruses.

episodes.title: Influenza
episodes.plot: The White Blood Cell meets a Naive T Cell who's scared of the invading influenza virus. Luckily the Macrophage and Killer T Cells are there.

episodes.title: Food Poisoning
episodes.plot: When a bacteria appears near the stomach wall, White Blood Cell rushes to the scene. Eosinophil is already there, but she isn't powerful enough.

episodes.title: Cedar Pollen Allergies
episodes.plot: It's cedar pollen season, and allergens are invading. As the Mast Cell produces histamines, the Memory T Cell insists the worst is yet to come.

episodes.title: Erythroblasts and Myelocytes
episodes.plot: Red Blood Cell recalls her past as a young Erythoblast in the red bone marrow. Always getting lost even then, a certain Myelocyte once helped her out.

episodes.title: Cancer Cell
episodes.plot: NK Cell calls a common cell's bluff: turns out he's Cancer Cell bent on spreading through the body via unchecked cellular proliferation. This means war.

episodes.title: Blood Circulation
episodes.plot: Red Blood Cell wants to make it through the circulatory system all by herself, though she keeps getting lost. White Blood Cell keeps an eye on her.

episodes.title: Thymocyte
episodes.plot: The Helper T Cell and the Killer T Cell seem like polar opposites, but long ago in the thymus, they were both just young T cells with a lot to learn.

episodes.title: Staphylococcus Aureus
episodes.plot: After a Monocyte rescues Red Blood Cell from a germ, she heads to the nasal cavity for a warm bath -- just in time for a Staphylococcus Aureus attack.

episodes.title: Heat Stroke
episodes.plot: Red Blood Cell heads to the epidermis to cool the body. As heat stroke symptoms worsen, White Blood Cell struggles to fight invading bacillus cereus.

episodes.title: Hemorrhagic Shock (Part I)
episodes.plot: Red Blood Cell gets her very own rookie to train, but her nerves make her even more inefficient. When a crisis strikes, however, she knows her job.

episodes.title: Hemorrhagic Shock (Part II)
episodes.plot: As hemorrhagic shock continues, the number of red blood cells decreases. Red Blood Cell and her rookie continue their job, but it may be too late.

episodes.title: OVA: Cold Syndrome
episodes.plot: A mysterious cell wearing a stylish hat appears before the regular cells, who are bored with just the same (cell division) work over and over again, every day. This mysterious cell lures the regular cells into a mischievous scheme against White Blood Cell and Killer T Cell. The regular cells enjoy working out their everyday, pent-up frustration, but just who exactly is this cell wearing a stylish hat?
